                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13390915/comment/17384223",
                    "id": "17384223",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jonkeane",
                        "name": "jonkeane",
                        "key": "jonkeane",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34057",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34057",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34057",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34057"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Keane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "This is not the exact same, but could be solved at the same time: Should we use {{-t}} as the short flag for both {{arrow-sha}} and {{github-token}}\u00a0(and also target directory, but I think that's a bit less of a concern and didn't cause the confusion in ARROW-13379) \r\n\r\n{code}\r\n@click.option('--arrow-sha', '-t', default=None,\r\n              help='Set commit SHA or Tag name explicitly, e.g. f67a515, '\r\n                   'apache-arrow-0.11.1.')\r\n{code}\r\nhttps://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/master/dev/archery/archery/crossbow/cli.py#L96-L98\r\n\r\n{code} \r\n@click.option('--github-token', '-t', default=None,\r\n              envvar=\"CROSSBOW_GITHUB_TOKEN\",\r\n              help='OAuth token for GitHub authentication')\r\n{code}\r\nhttps://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/master/dev/archery/archery/crossbow/cli.py#L33-L35",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jonkeane",
                        "name": "jonkeane",
                        "key": "jonkeane",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34057",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34057",
